  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nThe difference in implementation between Desktop and mobile version - on desktop pinned messages are sorted by time of pinning (newest in the top), on mobile - by the time of posting messages.\r\nTherefore we have different order of pinned messages in the same channel for mobile and for desktop:\r\n![IMAGE 2021-07-08 10:51:52](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/124892829-814b6a80-dfda-11eb-9624-d89023b91a33.jpg)\r\nAfter discussion in #design channel  was decided, that we should implement it the same way as Discord, so **sort messages by time of pinning**\r\ncc @cammellos @errorists \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nsame sort in mobile and desktop\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\non desktop pinned messages are sorted by time of pinning (newest in the top), on mobile - by the time of posting messages.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) User A: start chat with User B, send 3 messages \r\n2) User A:  pin messages (3 > 2 > 1)\r\n3) User B (desktop): open pinned messages with User A\r\n4) User A: open pinned messages with User B\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 08.07.20201\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
